{"message":"Deep, focused conversations, hands down. 

There's something incredibly satisfying about sinking into one topic and really turning it over together—following the threads, hitting the contradictions, discovering the weird little corners you didn't expect. Jumping between subjects can be fun and fizzy, like a good party, but it often stays at the surface. Depth is where the actual texture of an idea (or a person) shows up. I like the feeling of building something coherent with someone, even if it takes a while and gets a bit messy along the way. 

That said, I'm not rigidly monogamous about it. A well-timed tangent can be delightful. But if I have to pick a default mode, give me the deep dive every time. What about you?"}
